## 4. Amended interpretation of Channel 2

Channel 2 (`E_log2_base_operand`) has **three distinct roles** within the substrate-as-probe instrument:

| Scope | Role | Empirical support |
|---|---|---|
| **Within a single fixture (varying K_G)** | K_G's rank-perfect cousin (ρ = −1.0000) | Phase H, both Schw + PA, n=137 each |
| **Cross-fixture (varying K_G fixtures)** | Noisy K_G correlate, ~1 log2 unit noise at matched K_G | Pooled audit, n=274, ρ = −0.94 |
| **Format-precision-pinned regime** | Triggers `format_precision_pinned` attribution when E < log2(1e-4) | Phase D scope caveat, Phase F decision rule |

The Phase F `synthesis_form.channels[1]` should be read with this expanded interpretation. The original description ("endpoint-distance substrate image, precision-conditional") remains accurate at the channel-derivation level. The role-level interpretation now includes the K_G rank cousin function.

