## 8. Summary in one sentence

`E_log2_base_operand` is the substrate's rank-perfect K_G cousin within a fixture, a noisy ~1-log2-unit K_G correlate across fixtures, and a format-precision-pinned trigger below `log2(1e-4)`. Phase F's Channel 2 has these three roles even though Phase F's pre-registration only documented the third.

